{"id":826,"parent_id":0,"book_id":8,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":826,"title":"Mary","subtitle":"","short_title":"Mary","uri":"/scriptures/bd/mary","content":[["div",{"id":"t1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/mary.t1","order":".000.2167"},[".title","Mary"],["div",{"id":"p1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/mary.p1","order":".000.2168"},"(1) Mother of Jesus. The virgin, cousin of Elisabeth (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/1.36"},"Luke 1:36"],"); betrothed to Joseph (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/1.18"},"Matt. 1:18"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/1.27"},"Luke 1:27"],"); the Annunciation (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/1.26-38"},"26–38"],"); visits Elisabeth (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/1.40-45"},"40–45"],"); magnifies the Lord (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/1.46-55"},"46–55"],"); returns (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/1.56"},"56"],"); Joseph warned not to put her away (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/1.18-25"},"Matt. 1:18–25"],"); goes to Bethlehem with Joseph (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/2.4-5"},"Luke 2:4–5"],"); the Nativity (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/2.7,16"},"7, 16"],"); visit of the shepherds (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/2.16-20"},"16–20"],"); the Purification (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/2.21-38"},"2:21–38"],"); the Magi visit (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/2.11"},"Matt. 2:11"],"); in Egypt (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/2.13-14"},"13–14"],"); returns to Nazareth (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/2.19-23"},"19–23"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/2.39"},"Luke 2:39"],"); goes up to the Passover (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/2.41-52"},"41–52"],"); at the wedding at Cana (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/2.2-5"},"John 2:2–5"],"). Other references during our Lord’s ministry include",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/12.46"},"Matt. 12:46"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/13.54-55"},"13:54–55"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/3.31-32"},"Mark 3:31–32"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/6.3"},"6:3"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/8.19"},"Luke 8:19"],". She was entrusted to John (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/19.25-26"},"John 19:25–26"],") and was with the Apostles after the Ascension (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/acts/1.14"},"Acts 1:14"],"). There is no trustworthy history of her later years. Latter-day revelation confirms the biblical account and affirms that Mary was a pure and a chosen vessel and the mother of the Son of God in the flesh (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/1-ne/11.13-20"},"1 Ne. 11:13–20"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/3.8"},"Mosiah 3:8"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/7.10"},"Alma 7:10"],")."],["div",{"id":"p2","uri":"/scriptures/bd/mary.p2","order":".000.2169"},"(2) Sister of Lazarus and Martha. Sat at Jesus’ feet (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/10.39,42"},"Luke 10:39, 42"],"); sent for Jesus after the death of Lazarus (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/11.1-45"},"John 11:1–45"],"); anointed Jesus with ointment (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/12.3-8"},"John 12:3–8"],")."],["div",{"id":"p3","uri":"/scriptures/bd/mary.p3","order":".000.2170"},"(3) The mother of James and Joses, at the cross (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/27.56"},"Matt. 27:56"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/15.40"},"Mark 15:40"],"); perhaps the same Mary called the wife of Cleophas (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/19.25"},"John 19:25"],"); at the burial (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/27.61"},"Matt. 27:61"],"); “the other Mary” (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/15.47"},"Mark 15:47"],"); at the tomb in the morning (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/28.1"},"Matt. 28:1"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/16.1"},"Mark 16:1"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/24.10"},"Luke 24:10"],")."],["div",{"id":"p4","uri":"/scriptures/bd/mary.p4","order":".000.2171"},"(4) Mother of Mark (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/acts/12.12"},"Acts 12:12"],")."]]],"refs":null}
